         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Newyearsday ¶ 1882. ¶  ¶ In first instance, reverend and venerable friend, let me offer my felicitation to the new year; may it be to you and your florishing family one of health, happiness and again ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.01.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Miles Berkeley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Natural History Museum, London, Botany Library, Berkeley correspondence, vol. 9.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Newyearsday</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1882.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In first instance, reverend and venerable friend, let me offer my felicitation to the new year; may it be to you and your florishing family one of health, happiness and again also to you one of scientific triumphs!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am sad to learn of the demise of your sister, which loss after providence granted the Lady life through so many years and after she having been your companion through nearly a century you must feel much indeed!<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Charlotte Ann Berkeley, married name Bradley (10 April 1798 –19 October 1881).</p>
               </note> – But you have in this sadness the consolation of the support of younger members of your family, and can divert to other thoughts through the science on which you have shed so much lustre! I was glad to receive the extra-prints of your valuable 2. article on my fungs, especially in reference to <name key="Inoderma">Inoderma</name>.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Berkeley (1881).</p>
               </note> My own mycologic collection here is very limited, representing only a small share of the species procured by me. Hence I was totally in the dark about some of the genera &amp; species til now. I had just time to add to the last proofsheets of a systematic Index of genera of Australian plants <name key="Inoderma">Inoderma</name>, <name key="Phillipsea">Phillipsea</name> (there is already a genus Phillipsia) and <name key="Mycothozetia">Mycothozetia</name>.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See B82.13.08; B82.01.06. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Mycothozetia">Mycothozetia</name> nivea</seg> is listed in B81.13.12, but is not listed in <ref target="http://www.indexfungorum.org/"
                          rend="Internet%20link"
                          style="color: #0563c1; ">
                        <seg rend="Internet%20link" style="color: #0563c1; ">www.indexfungorum.org</seg>
                     </ref>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(viewed 12 December 2003); <seg style="font-style: italic; ">T</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">hozetia nivea</seg> was described by Berkeley &amp; Mueller in Berkeley (1881), p. 388.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Poor Dr Cooke<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mordecai Cooke.</p>
               </note> seems in very precarious health. perhaps Sir Joseph Hooker would send him on a mycologic errand to Central America.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall occasionally venture, til Dr Cooke is quite in the position again to work, to send you fungs, of which I do not want in all cases the names, but merely information on such, which are in a good state for examination and easily recognized.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to M. Berkeley, 8 October 1881 (in this edition as 81-10-08a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Let me hope that your excellent Lady will be fully restored to health.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Cecilia Emma Berkeley, Miles Berkeley's wife, died on 11 December 1881.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
